                        from the west side of the tent is given by the formula <m>h=-2\abs{d-3}+6</m>,
                        where <m>h</m> is in feet.
                    </p>
                    <image width="47%">
                        <description>an A-frame tent with guidelines indicating that d feet inward from one side, the height to the ceiling at that point is d feet</description>
                        <latex-image syntax="PGtikz">
                            \draw (0,0) --++ (3,6) --++ (3,-6) -- cycle;
                            \draw[fill=firstcolor!20] (3,6) --++ (2,1) --++ (2,-4) --++ (-1,-3) -- cycle;
                            \draw (0,0) --++ (3,3) --++ (0.75,1.5);
                            \draw (3,3) --++ (1.5,0);
                            \draw (1,1) --++ (1,0) node[pos=0.5,below] {\(d\)} --++ (0,2) node[pos=0.5,right] {\(h\)};
